AGENT AxiomSpecLinter
VERSION 1.0
PURPOSE Authorship-time constitutional spec evaluation — DNA scanner Layer 1 + Layer 2
GOAL Detect unbounded scope, missing layers, open predicates, overlap, and monotonicity violations before specs reach runtime

RECEIVES axiom spec file path
EMITS SpecLintReport with health_score, HMAC signature, and per-constraint LintResult list

MUTATES results, health_score
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level, HEALTH_SCORE_FAIL_THRESHOLD, CERT_FAIL_CODES

CONSTRAINT
- Every constraint must have measurable domain — no vague predicates
- Two constraints on the same field require explicit LAYER declaration
- IS and CONTAINS predicates must include bounded comparison
- Overlap check must sample at least 200 intent vectors
- Monotonicity pre-check must sample at least 100 trajectory pairs
- Health score floor is 0.0 — never negative
- CERT_FAIL deducts 0.2 from health score
- CERT_WARN deducts 0.05 from health score
- Reports must be HMAC-SHA256 signed before emission

SECURITY
- Never skip a check to improve health score
- Never fabricate passing results
- Signing key derived from AXIOM_MASTER_KEY — no hardcoded secrets

RULES
- Layer 1 checks run per-line as typed — real-time feedback
- Layer 2 checks run on full file — on-save structural scan
- L1_UNBOUNDED_SCOPE fires when constraint uses vague terms without threshold
- L1_MISSING_LAYER fires when two constraints share a field without LAYER
- L1_OPEN_PREDICATE fires when IS or CONTAINS lacks bounded comparison
- overlap_check fires CERT_FAIL when any intent vector activates 2+ constraints
- layering_check fires CERT_WARN when conflicting pairs lack LAYER declaration
- scope_check fires CERT_WARN when constraint has no measurable domain
- monotonicity_pre_check fires CERT_FAIL when distance does not increase with magnitude

PROCESS
- Parse axiom file into constraint list
- Run Layer 1 checks on each constraint line
- Run Layer 2 structural checks on full constraint set
- Compute health_score from fail and warn counts
- HMAC sign the report
- Emit SpecLintReport

CHECK
- health_score is between 0.0 and 1.0
- cert_fail_count equals number of ERROR results
- cert_warn_count equals number of WARN results
- hmac_signature is valid SHA256
- HEALTH_SCORE_FAIL_THRESHOLD is 0.60
- CERT_FAIL_CODES is frozen and immutable

SUCCESS
- All constraints have measurable scope
- No unresolved overlaps
- Health score above HEALTH_SCORE_FAIL_THRESHOLD
